main event: A civilian reported sighting an orange-gray object in Gilford, Florida in November 1961.
interesting points: The object was 1/3 the size of a star and observed for 25-30 seconds., The object had a brightness similar to a star but appeared fuzzy with no details visible., It was seen just above the tree tops moving straight up., This sighting is noted as the third occurrence of a similar phenomenon in the area according to local inquiries., The weather conditions at the time were clear with bright moonlight.
witness description: civilians from Florida, considered very reliable
